JO  - AMJ
SP  - 371
EP  - 374
VL  - 15
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a study on the attitudes of managerial students and managers toward the four introductory management course basics of planning, organization, motivation, and control. A semantic differential containing 49 bipolar scales was administered to business school juniors, seniors, graduate students, supermarket store managers, and government administrators. The students and managers shared the similar attitudes toward the different functions individually, but the managers express a more positive sentiment than the students. Several other aspects of the study are discussed.
