TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Method for Evaluating Readings Books
AU  - Gustafson, David P.
Y1  - 1972/09/01
PY  - 1972
DA  - 1972/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254867
DO  - 10.5465/254867
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 385
EP  - 388
VL  - 15
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a method for evaluating and reviewing books of compiled readings or readings books, which can be used in conjecture with standard reviewing methods. This method evaluates the newness of information compiled into these types of books, by comparing the citation decay curves of a specific readings book with other similar books. The books tested in this study are in the areas of Organization and Administration, Marketing, and Finance.Because decay rates vary between the different literature fields, comparisons must be made between books in the same field. The author points out that while this method is useful when combined with other methods, it should not a good method when used by itself.
AB  - The article presents a method for evaluating and reviewing books of compiled readings or readings books, which can be used in conjecture with standard reviewing methods. This method evaluates the newness of information compiled into these types of books, by comparing the citation decay curves of a specific readings book with other similar books. The books tested in this study are in the areas of Organization and Administration, Marketing, and Finance.Because decay rates vary between the different literature fields, comparisons must be made between books in the same field. The author points out that while this method is useful when combined with other methods, it should not a good method when used by itself.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/254867
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/254867
Y2  - 2026/04/24
